A senior Lands official in Kajiado town was almost lynched by residents last Friday. Registrar David Nyandoro and other staff locked themselves in the office. County commissioner Harsama Kello had to intervene.Residents accused Nyandoro and other staff of corruption, rudeness and poor service.They complained it takes up to three months for them to obtain results of land searches. Search results should ideally be ready in a week.The residents also said it takes about a year to get a land transfer document.Kello, whose office is metres away from the Lands registry, went to the scene after being told residents stormed the office.Residents demanded that Nyandoro be sacked.Kello escorted staff out of the office, then addressed residents. He said officers will investigate graft claims. Kello ordered the office closed indefinitely for shortage of staff.